WEBVTT

1
00:01:18.913 --> 00:01:21.381
<i>It's not easy
to move past certain things.</i>

2
00:01:23.317 --> 00:01:25.785
<i>I don't know how
anyone ever could.</i>

3
00:01:27.687 --> 00:01:28.822
<i>Especially this...</i>

4
00:01:38.632 --> 00:01:41.735
<i>75% of the world. maybe more.</i>

5
00:01:41.801 --> 00:01:42.903
<i>We still don't know.</i>

6
00:01:44.638 --> 00:01:45.639
<i>Gone.</i>

7
00:01:53.780 --> 00:01:55.415
<i>Five years since impact.</i>

8
00:01:55.482 --> 00:01:58.218
<i>but Clarke
wasn't done with us yet.</i>

9
00:01:58.285 --> 00:02:01.055
<i>Fragments stuck in our orbit.</i>

10
00:02:01.121 --> 00:02:03.157
<i>pelting us without warning.</i>

11
00:02:04.291 --> 00:02:06.226
<i>We tried rebuilding.</i>

12
00:02:06.293 --> 00:02:07.761
<i>but the world wasn't ready.</i>

13
00:02:09.129 --> 00:02:11.431
<i>Forcing us back inside.</i>

14
00:02:14.068 --> 00:02:16.070
<i>Radiation hit
differently everywhere.</i>

15
00:02:17.037 --> 00:02:19.306
<i>Most places burned out.</i>

16
00:02:19.373 --> 00:02:23.343
<i>Others. for reasons we don't
understand. stayed green.</i>

17
00:02:25.745 --> 00:02:29.649
<i>Life. finding a way
through the contamination.</i>

18
00:02:57.677 --> 00:02:59.313
<i>Our bunker's holding on.</i>

19
00:03:02.116 --> 00:03:03.550
<i>We're doing the best we can.</i>

20
00:03:06.586 --> 00:03:08.555
<i>It's not easy
living underground.</i>

21
00:03:11.025 --> 00:03:12.926
<i>But we find joy when we can.</i>

22
00:03:15.395 --> 00:03:16.563
<i>Together.</i>

23
00:03:46.160 --> 00:03:48.162
Microphone check.
One. two. One. two.

24
00:03:51.098 --> 00:03:52.332
<i>Loud and clear. John.</i>

25
00:03:54.468 --> 00:03:56.770
You know what I woke up
thinking about today?

26
00:03:58.805 --> 00:03:59.773
<i>Let's hear it.</i>

27
00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:03.543
Biscuits and gravy.

28
00:04:03.610 --> 00:04:05.779
<i>That'd be nice.</i>

29
00:04:05.845 --> 00:04:08.215
<i>I'd trade my left arm
for a decent cup of coffee.</i>

30
00:04:10.117 --> 00:04:11.718
Peckman's Diner
made the best.

31
00:04:11.785 --> 00:04:14.054
Across the street
from Piedmont Park.

32
00:04:14.121 --> 00:04:16.623
Walk over for one
of those summer concerts.

33
00:04:16.690 --> 00:04:18.458
Blue sky. grass. people.

34
00:04:19.193 --> 00:04:20.794
Beer.

35
00:04:20.860 --> 00:04:22.196
<i>Sounds like paradise.</i>

36
00:04:22.262 --> 00:04:23.363
Oh. it was.

37
00:04:26.032 --> 00:04:29.269
Jesus.
Another fissure's opened up.

38
00:04:29.336 --> 00:04:31.037
<i>More lava?</i>

39
00:04:31.105 --> 00:04:32.872
Yeah. and they're
getting bigger.

40
00:04:58.732 --> 00:05:01.034
Okay. looks like we've got
a few lifeboats.

41
00:05:05.205 --> 00:05:06.540
And another ghost ship.

42
00:05:07.474 --> 00:05:09.209
A destroyer.

43
00:05:09.276 --> 00:05:12.078
<i>Nice.
Feelin' lucky today?</i>

44
00:05:12.146 --> 00:05:13.647
Always. I'm starting
with the lifeboats.

45
00:05:13.713 --> 00:05:15.149
see what's there.

46
00:05:15.215 --> 00:05:16.216
<i>Good luck out there.</i>

47
00:05:34.901 --> 00:05:36.470
Heading to the destroyer.

48
00:05:40.474 --> 00:05:43.443
<i>We're seeing
a pressure storm building off the coast.</i>

49
00:05:43.510 --> 00:05:45.044
<i>but it looks like
you've got a little time.</i>

50
00:05:45.111 --> 00:05:46.913
I won't hang around.

51
00:06:07.201 --> 00:06:08.101
Jackpot.

52
00:06:16.776 --> 00:06:18.111
Entering the bridge.

53
00:06:23.317 --> 00:06:24.951
Oh. I've found something else.

54
00:06:25.952 --> 00:06:27.020
<i>What is it. John?</i>

55
00:06:28.922 --> 00:06:30.490
The crew.

56
00:06:32.359 --> 00:06:33.360
<i>Shit.</i>

57
00:07:01.988 --> 00:07:03.823
Oh. how beautiful.

58
00:07:06.426 --> 00:07:09.296
<i>John...</i>

59
00:07:09.363 --> 00:07:13.400
<i>John. can you hear me?
John. can you hear me?</i>

60
00:07:13.467 --> 00:07:15.101
<i>That storm just took
a turn right for you.</i>

61
00:07:15.168 --> 00:07:17.571
<i>You'd better get outta there
now and get back here!</i>

62
00:07:17.637 --> 00:07:19.138
On my way.

63
00:07:19.205 --> 00:07:22.242
Exiting ship now.
How much time do I have?

64
00:07:22.309 --> 00:07:23.643
<i>None.
It's right on top of you.</i>

65
00:07:36.222 --> 00:07:38.492
Come on...

66
00:07:38.558 --> 00:07:40.894
I'm staying ahead of it.
but it's gaining.

67
00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:49.202
Shit. base...
This one's coming in fast!

68
00:07:52.171 --> 00:07:54.941
<i>John!
John. where are you?</i>

69
00:07:55.008 --> 00:07:56.876
I'm moving
as fast as I can!

70
00:08:02.181 --> 00:08:03.617
Open the east tunnel!

71
00:08:05.652 --> 00:08:08.154
Open the door!

72
00:08:08.221 --> 00:08:10.256
Open the door! Get it open!

73
00:08:14.661 --> 00:08:16.463
<i>The storm is too close!</i>

74
00:08:16.530 --> 00:08:17.764
<i>We have to close
the blast doors. John!</i>

75
00:08:17.831 --> 00:08:19.366
I can make it!

76
00:08:26.072 --> 00:08:27.874
Close. close. close!

77
00:08:27.941 --> 00:08:29.175
Go. go. go. go. go!

78
00:08:29.242 --> 00:08:30.544
<i>John. are you in?</i>

79
00:09:03.410 --> 00:09:05.078
<i>Bucharest. Romania.</i>

80
00:09:05.144 --> 00:09:07.246
<i>The city has been destroyed
by the earthquakes.</i>

81
00:09:07.313 --> 00:09:09.549
<i>We're trapped under...</i>

82
00:09:09.616 --> 00:09:11.351
<i>Mumbai. India.</i>

83
00:09:11.418 --> 00:09:13.219
<i>Salt water is still
rising fast.</i>

84
00:09:13.286 --> 00:09:15.254
FEMA planned for two years.

85
00:09:15.321 --> 00:09:17.524
We've stretched
our resources to five.

86
00:09:17.591 --> 00:09:19.258
So we're basically
running on fumes?

87
00:09:19.325 --> 00:09:22.429
Yes. We are getting too close.

88
00:09:22.496 --> 00:09:26.466
Hopefully in a year
we're outside planting.

89
00:09:28.334 --> 00:09:31.337
Well. we have
measured a 4% reduction

90
00:09:31.405 --> 00:09:34.508
in coulomb per kilogram
in the last three months.

91
00:09:34.574 --> 00:09:36.943
We still can't predict
when it'll be safe levels again. but...

92
00:09:37.010 --> 00:09:39.278
- But it's improving. yeah?
- Yes.

93
00:09:39.345 --> 00:09:40.947
Though that's mostly
off the coast.

94
00:09:41.014 --> 00:09:42.749
Yeah. Hopefully the winds
will eventually

95
00:09:42.816 --> 00:09:44.083
clear out the radiation.

96
00:09:44.150 --> 00:09:46.085
No. that's not exactly
how it works.

97
00:09:46.152 --> 00:09:48.388
Continuous radiation exposure.

98
00:09:48.455 --> 00:09:52.559
even at those low levels
still leads to fatality.

99
00:09:52.626 --> 00:09:54.728
We should discuss
our contingency plans.

100
00:09:54.794 --> 00:09:56.563
Okay. yeah. Um...

101
00:09:56.630 --> 00:09:59.899
Canada. and much
of the US. gone.

102
00:10:00.767 --> 00:10:02.001
Iceland. gone.

103
00:10:02.802 --> 00:10:04.738
Western Europe?

104
00:10:04.804 --> 00:10:06.773
There are reports
of fewer storms there. right?

105
00:10:06.840 --> 00:10:08.575
- Yes.
- But is the air safe?

106
00:10:10.009 --> 00:10:11.745
Safer than here.

107
00:10:11.811 --> 00:10:14.881
Didn't we just say that
dying slowly is still dying?

108
00:10:14.948 --> 00:10:17.150
I mean. am I right. Dr. Amina?

109
00:10:17.216 --> 00:10:20.019
- Isn't it the same over there?
- Yes.

110
00:10:23.189 --> 00:10:25.391
Dr. Amina. what's the latest
on the crater?

111
00:10:28.995 --> 00:10:31.230
Well. my colleagues
at other stations

112
00:10:31.297 --> 00:10:32.766
have theorized
the same thing.

113
00:10:32.832 --> 00:10:34.934
And I've run my
own calculations.

114
00:10:35.001 --> 00:10:36.436
We can't fully explain it.

115
00:10:36.503 --> 00:10:39.238
but it seems the size
and shape of the crater walls

116
00:10:39.305 --> 00:10:41.941
prevent the radioactive storms
from forming.

117
00:10:42.008 --> 00:10:43.610
This combined with its depth

118
00:10:43.677 --> 00:10:45.311
are what's making it
such a safe zone.

119
00:10:45.378 --> 00:10:46.179
We believe it's what's keeping

120
00:10:46.245 --> 00:10:48.314
the polluted air
from getting in.

121
00:10:48.381 --> 00:10:50.984
But. Dr. Amina.
even if it was real.

122
00:10:51.050 --> 00:10:53.487
it's in Southern France.

123
00:10:53.553 --> 00:10:55.354
How exactly
are we gonna get there?

124
00:10:55.421 --> 00:10:57.190
There have been
reports of fighting.

125
00:10:57.256 --> 00:10:59.325
insurgency. civil war.

126
00:10:59.392 --> 00:11:00.460
Europe is in chaos.

127
00:11:02.762 --> 00:11:05.231
Please let's...
Let's stick to reality.

128
00:11:10.604 --> 00:11:11.638
<i>Attention residents.</i>

129
00:11:11.705 --> 00:11:13.139
<i>this is your daily reminder</i>

130
00:11:13.206 --> 00:11:14.774
<i>to report any malfunctioning
air filtration...</i>

131
00:11:14.841 --> 00:11:16.810
<i>Please ration
carefully and only...</i>

132
00:11:16.876 --> 00:11:19.412
<i>There's people here
who say it's the new normal.</i>

133
00:11:20.880 --> 00:11:22.081
Well. we're going on...

134
00:11:23.116 --> 00:11:25.151
- five years now?
- Mmm-hmm.

135
00:11:25.218 --> 00:11:26.419
So it isn't all that new.

136
00:11:27.587 --> 00:11:29.222
And it definitely
ain't normal.

137
00:11:29.288 --> 00:11:31.558
You know.
it's no accident there were

138
00:11:31.625 --> 00:11:33.159
twice as many
therapists selected

139
00:11:33.226 --> 00:11:35.294
as there were surgeons.

140
00:11:35.361 --> 00:11:38.665
People are dealing with an
incredible amount of trauma.

141
00:11:38.732 --> 00:11:40.634
Why does everybody
pretend like they're not. huh?

142
00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:41.835
- Do you?
- Pretend?

143
00:11:41.901 --> 00:11:43.069
Mmm-hmm.

144
00:11:44.938 --> 00:11:45.839
Sometimes.

145
00:11:47.273 --> 00:11:49.308
Maybe you should stop.

146
00:11:49.375 --> 00:11:50.844
Well. maybe you can recommend
a good therapist

147
00:11:50.910 --> 00:11:51.911
that can help me with that.

148
00:11:52.879 --> 00:11:53.813
Mine's pretty good.

149
00:11:59.886 --> 00:12:01.487
So. uh...

150
00:12:03.389 --> 00:12:05.692
Allison. Nathan. how are they?

151
00:12:07.260 --> 00:12:08.261
They're getting by.

152
00:12:08.327 --> 00:12:09.462
I think. I hope.

153
00:12:11.665 --> 00:12:14.167
Openness is important. Uh...

154
00:12:15.935 --> 00:12:17.871
Well. they're pretty open
with me.

155
00:12:19.472 --> 00:12:20.640
I meant the other way around.

156
00:12:36.089 --> 00:12:37.490
Seems like there's been
more of those lately.

157
00:12:39.425 --> 00:12:42.295
The tectonic plates
are shifting again.

158
00:12:42.361 --> 00:12:45.064
It's triggering a lot
of activity in this region.

159
00:12:45.131 --> 00:12:46.866
This bunker survived Clarke.

160
00:12:46.933 --> 00:12:48.702
It'll survive tremors.

161
00:12:48.768 --> 00:12:51.070
There's one more thing
we should discuss.

162
00:12:51.137 --> 00:12:53.907
The distress signal
we received from outside.

163
00:12:53.973 --> 00:12:56.242
We cannot afford to feed
50 more mouths.

164
00:12:56.309 --> 00:12:58.077
We can't afford five.

165
00:12:58.144 --> 00:12:59.545
I know.
but these people are living

166
00:12:59.613 --> 00:13:01.314
in caves and mineshafts.

167
00:13:01.380 --> 00:13:03.650
Yes. and we don't know
if they're bringing disease

168
00:13:03.717 --> 00:13:06.252
or how much radiation
they've absorbed.

169
00:13:06.319 --> 00:13:08.154
Okay. We just let them die.

170
00:13:10.824 --> 00:13:14.093
We tell them we are not
currently in a position

171
00:13:14.160 --> 00:13:15.094
to be of assistance.

172
00:13:16.896 --> 00:13:18.264
- Yeah?
- No.

173
00:13:18.331 --> 00:13:20.767
We put it to a vote
like everything else.

174
00:13:20.834 --> 00:13:22.836
Motion to send out
a rescue party?

175
00:13:24.203 --> 00:13:25.204
I second.

176
00:13:36.582 --> 00:13:37.851
General...

177
00:13:37.917 --> 00:13:39.518
The vote stands.

178
00:13:39.585 --> 00:13:41.921
We'll send out
the Snowcat tomorrow.

179
00:13:43.589 --> 00:13:46.459
And as we look
at the northern sky.

180
00:13:46.525 --> 00:13:49.495
which constellation is this?

181
00:13:49.562 --> 00:13:51.564
- Gemini?
- No. No. not Gemini.

182
00:13:52.365 --> 00:13:53.366
Nathan?

183
00:13:55.068 --> 00:13:57.303
Oh. um. it's Cassiopeia.

184
00:13:57.370 --> 00:14:00.139
You can tell by its W-shape.

185
00:14:00.206 --> 00:14:02.441
Why do we have to
learn so much about the stars?

186
00:14:02.508 --> 00:14:03.877
Well. maybe
we should have paid

187
00:14:03.943 --> 00:14:05.611
a little more attention
to them in the past.

188
00:14:05.679 --> 00:14:07.580
Clarke wasn't a star.
it was a comet.

189
00:14:08.214 --> 00:14:09.215
Still is.

190
00:14:09.282 --> 00:14:11.450
But it already hit the ground.

191
00:14:11.517 --> 00:14:12.551
The biggest
part of it did.

192
00:14:12.618 --> 00:14:15.655
but the smaller bits
that didn't.

193
00:14:15.722 --> 00:14:18.658
they got caught
in our gravitational field.

194
00:14:18.725 --> 00:14:21.795
Created what is known
as a ghost ring.

195
00:14:31.204 --> 00:14:34.774
<i>* You catch my breath
on the morning light *</i>

196
00:14:34.841 --> 00:14:39.312
<i>* A thousand times
and it still surprises me *</i>

197
00:14:39.378 --> 00:14:45.418
<i>* I fall asleep where
I like to think our dreams *</i>

198
00:14:45.484 --> 00:14:46.419
<i>* Collide... *</i>

199
00:14:48.287 --> 00:14:50.223
Lars. what is this shit?

200
00:14:50.289 --> 00:14:52.692
What? It's classical
rock and roll.

201
00:14:52.759 --> 00:14:57.430
If you mean classic rock.
then this ain't it.

202
00:14:57.496 --> 00:15:00.934
Gimme the Stones.
the Allman Brothers...

203
00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:04.037
Michael McDonald.
now that's classical rock.

204
00:15:05.471 --> 00:15:07.440
Billy Ocean. Also pretty cool.

205
00:15:10.910 --> 00:15:13.379
Just turn
the valve on already.

206
00:15:22.756 --> 00:15:25.024
Come on. baby. Here we go!

207
00:15:31.497 --> 00:15:33.800
Whoo! Back in business!

208
00:15:33.867 --> 00:15:36.102
Nice!

209
00:15:36.169 --> 00:15:37.670
We can drink some water again.

210
00:15:40.706 --> 00:15:41.674
Mom...

211
00:15:42.876 --> 00:15:44.310
Mom. I can explain.

212
00:15:44.377 --> 00:15:45.945
Nathan. I don't
want to hear it!

213
00:15:46.012 --> 00:15:47.981
You hear how your dad's
coughing at night. right?

214
00:15:48.047 --> 00:15:48.748
Yeah.

215
00:15:49.883 --> 00:15:51.250
Get in.

216
00:15:53.519 --> 00:15:55.688
Oh. I hate this place.

217
00:15:58.691 --> 00:16:00.693
Come here. I know.

218
00:16:04.330 --> 00:16:06.499
It's okay.

219
00:16:12.071 --> 00:16:13.472
- Do you know it?
- Yes. of course!

220
00:16:13.539 --> 00:16:15.308
Impossible.

221
00:16:15.374 --> 00:16:17.010
Hey. what did I miss?

222
00:16:17.076 --> 00:16:18.845
He has never heard this song.

223
00:16:18.912 --> 00:16:20.847
You've never heard
this song before?

224
00:16:20.914 --> 00:16:22.648
- I like it though. huh?
- Yeah? Then come dance.

225
00:16:22.715 --> 00:16:24.283
Oh. okay. Let's...
I'm gonna dance

226
00:16:24.350 --> 00:16:25.484
to the song I've never heard.

227
00:16:25.551 --> 00:16:27.653
Good.

228
00:16:27.720 --> 00:16:30.189
Oh. I know
it's a little late. but...

229
00:16:30.256 --> 00:16:31.724
Da-da-da-dah.

230
00:16:32.992 --> 00:16:35.161
Happy belated Valentine's Day.

231
00:16:35.228 --> 00:16:37.797
Where'd you find it?

232
00:16:37.864 --> 00:16:40.166
In that destroyer.
Amongst some other stuff.

233
00:16:40.233 --> 00:16:42.768
I can finally fix my radio.

234
00:16:42.836 --> 00:16:44.971
What about the pressure pump
for desalination?

235
00:16:45.038 --> 00:16:46.105
General Sharpe was saying

236
00:16:46.172 --> 00:16:47.606
that the water levels
are getting low.

237
00:16:50.276 --> 00:16:51.544
I'm sorry.

238
00:16:53.012 --> 00:16:54.580
I love it. Thank you.

239
00:16:55.748 --> 00:16:59.018
- Whoo!
- Thank you.

240
00:16:59.085 --> 00:17:00.153
What about you. young man?
How was your day?

241
00:17:02.255 --> 00:17:03.356
Fine.

242
00:17:03.422 --> 00:17:04.790
Is there anything else

243
00:17:04.858 --> 00:17:06.392
you wanna say
to your father. Nathan?

244
00:17:08.594 --> 00:17:10.563
Security found him outside.

245
00:17:11.264 --> 00:17:13.166
Outside. outside?

246
00:17:13.232 --> 00:17:14.667
Yep.

247
00:17:14.733 --> 00:17:16.169
Are you kidding me?

248
00:17:16.235 --> 00:17:17.670
How long
were you out there for?

249
00:17:17.736 --> 00:17:19.072
Only a few minutes.

250
00:17:19.138 --> 00:17:20.573
- Did you wear a mask?
- Yeah.

251
00:17:20.639 --> 00:17:22.075
And there wasn't a storm.

252
00:17:22.141 --> 00:17:24.710
It's too dangerous for you
to be going outside!

253
00:17:24.777 --> 00:17:26.645
- What are you thinking?
- I know.

254
00:17:26.712 --> 00:17:28.314
You told me.
the radiation. the ash.

255
00:17:28.381 --> 00:17:29.415
I understand.

256
00:17:31.217 --> 00:17:34.687
Look. son. I know how much
it sucks being down here.

257
00:17:34.753 --> 00:17:36.389
- I get it.
- Try being 15.

258
00:17:36.455 --> 00:17:38.157
Yeah. well. you're not
listening to me!

259
00:17:40.894 --> 00:17:42.395
- Look. wait...
- Can I be excused?

260
00:17:50.269 --> 00:17:52.571
He's just trying to figure
things out. I guess.

261
00:17:52.638 --> 00:17:53.739
- No. no...
- He's also sensitive.

262
00:17:53.806 --> 00:17:54.840
No. he's being an idiot.

263
00:17:55.608 --> 00:17:56.609
Like you.

264
00:17:59.245 --> 00:18:00.013
Going outside?

265
00:18:01.280 --> 00:18:02.348
Oh...

266
00:18:03.649 --> 00:18:05.384
Yeah.

267
00:18:05.451 --> 00:18:06.652
Takes after his father.

268
00:18:13.726 --> 00:18:14.894
<i>* Everyone I know... *</i>

269
00:18:16.695 --> 00:18:19.065
- Come on.
- No. no. Allison. no.

270
00:18:19.132 --> 00:18:22.768
If your lady asks for a dance.
how can you say no?

271
00:18:22.835 --> 00:18:24.070
- Thank you. Lars.
- Thank you. Thank you. Lars.

272
00:18:24.137 --> 00:18:24.870
Come on.

273
00:18:26.305 --> 00:18:27.540
All right. all right.

274
00:18:27.606 --> 00:18:29.075
<i>* If it takes all night *</i>

275
00:18:30.876 --> 00:18:34.013
<i>* That'll be all right *</i>

276
00:18:34.080 --> 00:18:37.416
<i>* If I can get you to smile
before I leave... *</i>

277
00:18:59.472 --> 00:19:00.773
Are you taking care
of yourself?

278
00:19:01.507 --> 00:19:03.742
Yeah... yeah.

279
00:19:16.455 --> 00:19:19.025
<i>Base. this is Rover One
returning with a full load.</i>

280
00:19:19.092 --> 00:19:20.826
<i>Are we ready to receive
the migrants?</i>

281
00:19:20.893 --> 00:19:23.029
Prepare to open
the West Tunnel ramp.

282
00:19:23.096 --> 00:19:24.430
Have the decontamination
teams ready.

283
00:19:24.497 --> 00:19:25.831
<i>Copy.</i>

284
00:19:25.898 --> 00:19:27.066
Come on. come on. come on.

285
00:19:29.168 --> 00:19:30.103
Morning. mate.

286
00:19:31.937 --> 00:19:33.939
I was thinking we. uh.

287
00:19:34.007 --> 00:19:35.908
start on the intake pump
today. Larsy.

288
00:19:37.576 --> 00:19:38.911
Tackle the rest after lunch?

289
00:19:47.386 --> 00:19:48.587
Shit.

290
00:19:51.490 --> 00:19:53.126
<i>Confirmed
personnel incoming...</i>

291
00:19:53.959 --> 00:19:55.494
Copy. Hold. One.

292
00:19:55.561 --> 00:19:57.496
Sir. seeking authorization
for a second trip.

293
00:19:57.563 --> 00:19:59.365
They left a lot
of people behind.

294
00:19:59.432 --> 00:20:00.299
A second trip?

295
00:20:04.037 --> 00:20:06.539
- No way.
- Before we make any decisions.

296
00:20:06.605 --> 00:20:08.474
let's just figure out exactly
what we're talking about.

297
00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:11.044
Weren't we discussing
limited resources?

298
00:20:11.110 --> 00:20:12.478
Where are they going to sleep?

299
00:20:12.545 --> 00:20:13.912
In your bed?

300
00:20:13.979 --> 00:20:16.649
If it's gonna save lives. yes.

301
00:20:16.715 --> 00:20:19.018
<i>...approach
...now.</i>

302
00:20:19.085 --> 00:20:20.886
Uh. bad copy.
Rover One. Repeat.

303
00:20:20.953 --> 00:20:21.987
<i>We don't have much time...</i>

304
00:20:22.055 --> 00:20:23.556
<i>Are we approved?</i>

305
00:20:23.622 --> 00:20:25.258
Hold tight.

306
00:20:25.324 --> 00:20:26.359
A reading on that...

307
00:20:26.425 --> 00:20:27.493
Rover One. repeat.

308
00:20:27.560 --> 00:20:28.961
Oh. Jesus!

309
00:20:40.273 --> 00:20:41.006
Oh!

310
00:21:03.196 --> 00:21:04.997
Lars. Lars...
Lars help me.

311
00:21:15.874 --> 00:21:17.276
You all right?

312
00:21:17.343 --> 00:21:18.644
<i>Attention all personnel...</i>

313
00:21:25.284 --> 00:21:26.785
Allison!

314
00:21:26.852 --> 00:21:28.020
Allison!

315
00:21:31.690 --> 00:21:34.059
Allison. you okay?

316
00:21:34.127 --> 00:21:36.028
There you go.
All right. You hurt?

317
00:21:38.197 --> 00:21:39.898
Okay. You all right?

318
00:21:39.965 --> 00:21:40.799
- Yeah...
- Let's get you up.

319
00:21:40.866 --> 00:21:42.268
Let's get...

320
00:21:45.304 --> 00:21:47.440
- Nathan... Nathan!
- We've gotta go. Now.

321
00:21:51.977 --> 00:21:53.112
- Do you seen him?
- No.

322
00:21:54.680 --> 00:21:55.848
Nathan!

323
00:21:55.914 --> 00:21:58.151
Dad!

324
00:21:58.217 --> 00:21:59.852
- I can't breathe.
- Are you hurt?

325
00:21:59.918 --> 00:22:01.854
- You can breathe.
- We've gotta get out of here!

326
00:22:01.920 --> 00:22:03.189
Yeah. let's pack our bags!

327
00:22:03.256 --> 00:22:04.623
Food. clothes.
Everything we've got.

328
00:22:04.690 --> 00:22:05.858
- Okay.
- All right. Nathan?

329
00:22:05.924 --> 00:22:06.792
I need you
to be with me. kiddo.

330
00:22:06.859 --> 00:22:07.860
You've got this. Nathan.

331
00:22:07.926 --> 00:22:09.162
Help your mum.
Pack your stuff.

332
00:22:09.228 --> 00:22:10.563
All right.
I'm gonna go get some masks.

333
00:22:11.330 --> 00:22:12.665
Pack your stuff.

334
00:22:12.731 --> 00:22:15.033
Take everything you need.
Get your insulin.

335
00:22:15.100 --> 00:22:16.169
As much as you can

336
00:22:16.235 --> 00:22:17.836
and you put it all
in the bag. okay?

337
00:22:17.903 --> 00:22:19.372
We're not coming back.

338
00:22:30.516 --> 00:22:32.485
Jacket. clothes...
anything that'll fit in there.

339
00:22:34.787 --> 00:22:38.191
Okay. I've got some masks.
There you go.

340
00:22:38.257 --> 00:22:40.459
Right. put this on.
Right. kiddo. Yep.

341
00:22:48.901 --> 00:22:50.336
- You good?
- Yeah. I'm good.

342
00:22:50.403 --> 00:22:51.470
You good?

343
00:22:59.077 --> 00:23:00.179
Let's go!

344
00:23:07.119 --> 00:23:08.887
I'm stuck!

345
00:23:08.954 --> 00:23:10.356
We're not gonna get
through here!

346
00:23:10.423 --> 00:23:12.525
- Where are we gonna go?
- To the East Tunnel!

347
00:23:12.591 --> 00:23:13.492
Shit! Go. go!

348
00:23:19.598 --> 00:23:21.367
It's collapsed!

349
00:23:21.434 --> 00:23:23.569
We don't have
any other choice!

350
00:23:32.945 --> 00:23:34.513
- John?
- Allison!

351
00:23:34.580 --> 00:23:36.915
- It's falling down!
- I've got you! Come on!

352
00:23:36.982 --> 00:23:38.884
All right. you're good.

353
00:23:38.951 --> 00:23:40.353
Come on. we've gotta go.
we've gotta go!

354
00:23:41.454 --> 00:23:42.821
Come on. come on!

355
00:23:45.090 --> 00:23:47.260
Okay. are we covered up
as much as possible?

356
00:23:47.326 --> 00:23:48.694
- Yes.
- Check your masks!

357
00:23:48.761 --> 00:23:49.528
Everything's good.

358
00:24:01.274 --> 00:24:02.341
Go. go. go!

359
00:24:13.319 --> 00:24:14.987
The radiation.
what do we do?

360
00:24:15.053 --> 00:24:16.322
We've gotta get off
this island.

361
00:24:16.389 --> 00:24:18.090
This way. to the beach.

362
00:24:34.039 --> 00:24:35.574
Nathan!
Where's Nathan?

363
00:24:36.842 --> 00:24:38.243
Where'd he go?

364
00:24:38.311 --> 00:24:40.178
- Nathan!
- Mom. Dad. over here!

365
00:24:40.245 --> 00:24:41.213
There!

366
00:24:42.848 --> 00:24:44.182
Doctor Amina!

367
00:24:44.249 --> 00:24:45.584
- You okay?
- Dr. Casey?

368
00:24:45.651 --> 00:24:46.852
Can you stand?

369
00:24:47.820 --> 00:24:49.021
Come on. let's get up.

370
00:24:49.087 --> 00:24:50.255
There's lifeboats
on the beach.

371
00:24:50.323 --> 00:24:51.390
Let's go. Let's go!

372
00:25:14.913 --> 00:25:17.316
All right. make sure
to follow me!

373
00:25:17.383 --> 00:25:18.884
There are more boats
at the end of the beach!

374
00:25:24.790 --> 00:25:25.824
Come on!

375
00:25:35.133 --> 00:25:36.134
Help!

376
00:25:37.570 --> 00:25:39.037
Help!

377
00:25:39.104 --> 00:25:39.838
- Just give it.
- No!

378
00:25:40.906 --> 00:25:42.207
John! Over here!

379
00:25:42.274 --> 00:25:43.976
Allison!

380
00:25:44.042 --> 00:25:45.644
Stop! Let him go!

381
00:25:54.887 --> 00:25:55.788
Stay back!

382
00:25:57.756 --> 00:25:59.725
There's one more! Come on!

383
00:25:59.792 --> 00:26:01.293
There's one more over there!

384
00:26:02.260 --> 00:26:03.328
Hurry!

385
00:26:06.799 --> 00:26:07.966
Come on!

386
00:26:11.804 --> 00:26:13.105
We've gotta go.
Come on!

387
00:26:14.507 --> 00:26:15.874
We've gotta go now!

388
00:26:15.941 --> 00:26:17.810
Okay! Go. go. go!

389
00:26:18.944 --> 00:26:20.446
No more! Shut the door!

390
00:26:20.513 --> 00:26:22.280
No! Let them in!
We can make room!

391
00:26:22.347 --> 00:26:24.016
No more!
We'll capsize like the others!

392
00:26:24.082 --> 00:26:25.718
Secure the hatch!

393
00:26:25.784 --> 00:26:27.119
We can't take any more.
I'm sorry!

394
00:26:27.185 --> 00:26:28.186
Don't leave us!

395
00:26:48.707 --> 00:26:50.042
You okay? All right.

396
00:26:52.978 --> 00:26:56.415
Wait! Wait! No!

397
00:26:56.482 --> 00:26:58.451
All right.
everybody okay?

398
00:27:02.855 --> 00:27:04.990
Dad! Dad!

399
00:27:05.057 --> 00:27:06.992
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

400
00:27:07.059 --> 00:27:08.427
Everybody. hold on!

401
00:27:27.045 --> 00:27:27.780
Oh. my God!

402
00:27:32.184 --> 00:27:34.019
Brace! Brace!

403
00:28:01.413 --> 00:28:02.648
You okay. Nathan?

404
00:28:02.715 --> 00:28:03.849
I'm good.

405
00:28:03.916 --> 00:28:04.983
It's gone.

406
00:28:06.051 --> 00:28:06.819
It's all gone.

407
00:28:42.154 --> 00:28:45.423
Hey. I think the air
quality's good. Better.

408
00:28:45.490 --> 00:28:46.959
- We can take off the masks?
- Yeah.

409
00:28:58.270 --> 00:28:59.605
- You all right?
- Yeah.

410
00:28:59.672 --> 00:29:01.273
Let me see you.

411
00:29:01.339 --> 00:29:02.340
Where do we go?

412
00:29:03.475 --> 00:29:05.744
There's nothing to go back to.

413
00:29:05.811 --> 00:29:07.680
Isn't Iceland
the closest place to here?

414
00:29:07.746 --> 00:29:09.381
Ice... Iceland's gone.

415
00:29:10.583 --> 00:29:11.784
Well. we need a destination.

416
00:29:11.850 --> 00:29:13.786
We just need to hit land.

417
00:29:13.852 --> 00:29:15.921
Clarke changed the direction
of the current.

418
00:29:15.988 --> 00:29:17.455
It's now flowing south.

419
00:29:17.522 --> 00:29:18.791
We have with us barely

420
00:29:18.857 --> 00:29:21.059
a week's supply
of MREs and water.

421
00:29:21.126 --> 00:29:23.562
I. uh... Europe is probably
our best bet.

422
00:29:23.629 --> 00:29:26.865
So. that's good.
Then we head southeast.

423
00:29:26.932 --> 00:29:28.801
Until we reach England.

424
00:29:28.867 --> 00:29:32.137
If we can get to London.
we can go to Mackenzie's.

425
00:29:32.204 --> 00:29:34.506
Perfect.
Should take less than a week.

426
00:29:35.107 --> 00:29:36.174
Pray we make it.

427
00:29:38.143 --> 00:29:38.877
Southeast.

428
00:30:16.982 --> 00:30:17.950
Okay.

429
00:30:19.217 --> 00:30:19.952
Try it now?

430
00:30:27.693 --> 00:30:29.261
All right.
Let me try one more thing.

431
00:30:29.327 --> 00:30:30.963
Okay.

432
00:30:34.833 --> 00:30:36.134
There she goes.

433
00:30:49.514 --> 00:30:51.449
How many fragments
do you think are up there?

434
00:30:54.753 --> 00:30:56.789
More than I can count.
that's for sure.

435
00:30:57.956 --> 00:30:59.591
And so at least 50.

436
00:31:02.961 --> 00:31:05.363
Whoa. That's Andromeda.

437
00:31:05.430 --> 00:31:08.867
- That's a whole other galaxy.
- Wow.

438
00:31:08.934 --> 00:31:10.836
I can't believe
I'm seeing the stars for real.

439
00:31:12.237 --> 00:31:13.638
It's pretty cool. huh?

440
00:31:15.207 --> 00:31:16.641
I hope you never lose that.

441
00:31:18.276 --> 00:31:20.612
That... wonder of yours.

442
00:31:30.756 --> 00:31:32.124
I wonder where
that's gonna hit.

443
00:31:49.407 --> 00:31:51.076
I'll take a look.

444
00:31:51.143 --> 00:31:51.944
It's not that.

445
00:31:54.079 --> 00:31:55.213
We're outta gas.

446
00:31:56.248 --> 00:31:57.883
And maybe we can ration...

447
00:31:57.950 --> 00:32:01.053
two more days
of water and MREs.

448
00:32:01.119 --> 00:32:02.654
We're at the mercy
of the current now.

449
00:32:08.260 --> 00:32:10.028
So wait.
where did you end up then?

450
00:32:10.095 --> 00:32:12.230
- We ended in Shenandoah.
- Really?

451
00:32:12.297 --> 00:32:14.066
Oh. you know. I've always
wanted to go there.

452
00:32:14.132 --> 00:32:15.533
- Yeah. it was great.
- Was it?

453
00:32:15.600 --> 00:32:16.869
My wife wanted to do
the whole trip. but I ended up

454
00:32:16.935 --> 00:32:19.604
cutting it short
so I could take a new job.

455
00:32:19.671 --> 00:32:22.240
Seemed like a big deal
at the time.

456
00:32:23.141 --> 00:32:24.209
Your wife.

457
00:32:24.276 --> 00:32:27.245
Did you lose her
leaving the bunker?

458
00:32:27.312 --> 00:32:29.915
No. I lost her getting...
getting to it.

459
00:32:45.063 --> 00:32:46.098
Need some...

460
00:32:47.132 --> 00:32:48.500
Oh. I need food.

461
00:32:51.703 --> 00:32:52.737
Crater.

462
00:32:52.805 --> 00:32:54.672
The crater has enough...

463
00:32:54.739 --> 00:32:56.608
Build a bunker. and...

464
00:32:58.243 --> 00:33:00.012
Swim...

465
00:33:00.078 --> 00:33:01.513
We need to make it.

466
00:33:11.924 --> 00:33:13.758
Oh. my God.
What did we hit?

467
00:33:13.826 --> 00:33:15.127
Oh. my God!

468
00:33:15.193 --> 00:33:16.761
- It's land. guys.
- What is that?

469
00:33:16.829 --> 00:33:18.130
We've hit land!

470
00:33:25.170 --> 00:33:27.039
That's the Liver Building.

471
00:33:27.105 --> 00:33:28.140
We're in Liverpool!

472
00:33:28.206 --> 00:33:28.941
- What?
- England!

473
00:33:30.275 --> 00:33:31.609
What?

474
00:33:31.676 --> 00:33:34.146
- What?
- In England? Oh. my God!

475
00:33:37.349 --> 00:33:40.285
The air's okay. for now.

476
00:33:40.352 --> 00:33:42.287
We'll need to find shelter.

477
00:33:42.354 --> 00:33:43.388
What did we hit?

478
00:33:54.599 --> 00:33:57.035
Oh. my God.

479
00:33:57.102 --> 00:33:59.171
Here. we're on a...
We're on a building top.

480
00:33:59.237 --> 00:34:00.973
Let's get these oars
and push us off.

481
00:34:05.143 --> 00:34:06.578
- You ready?
- Yeah.

482
00:34:13.485 --> 00:34:15.520
There's a road up ahead.
Lieutenant.

483
00:34:15.587 --> 00:34:16.821
Can you steer us
round that way?

484
00:34:16.889 --> 00:34:17.789
Okay.

485
00:34:37.175 --> 00:34:38.776
- Dan. you reverse.
- Yeah.

486
00:34:38.843 --> 00:34:40.312
- With the paddle.
- Yeah. got it.

487
00:34:50.822 --> 00:34:51.823
Oh. there we go.

488
00:34:57.129 --> 00:34:58.196
All right. let's go.

489
00:35:00.098 --> 00:35:01.233
Stay close.

490
00:35:01.299 --> 00:35:02.834
We don't know
what's out there.

491
00:35:05.770 --> 00:35:07.039
Come on. kiddo. Good stuff.

492
00:35:16.648 --> 00:35:19.217
It looks. uh. abandoned.

493
00:35:19.284 --> 00:35:20.953
All right.
first thing's first.

494
00:35:21.019 --> 00:35:23.721
we need to find some
food and water.

495
00:35:23.788 --> 00:35:26.458
And we can't stay up here
the whole time.

496
00:35:26.524 --> 00:35:29.427
so a proper place
for everybody to shelter.

497
00:35:29.494 --> 00:35:31.596
Wasn't there a bomb shelter
or a bunker in this area?

498
00:35:31.663 --> 00:35:34.266
Yeah. but we've never had
any contact with them.

499
00:35:34.332 --> 00:35:36.234
Still. we should try
to find it.

500
00:35:37.869 --> 00:35:39.171
Oh. look.
there's people there.

501
00:35:49.547 --> 00:35:51.416
Where are they?

502
00:35:51.483 --> 00:35:54.452
Where are your politicians?

503
00:35:54.519 --> 00:35:56.054
Your noble kings?

504
00:35:57.655 --> 00:35:59.791
They are all underground.

505
00:36:02.260 --> 00:36:04.696
Only the true God...

506
00:36:04.762 --> 00:36:06.198
How do they live outside?

507
00:36:06.264 --> 00:36:07.632
...since the beginning
of time...

508
00:36:07.699 --> 00:36:08.933
They probably
don't have a choice.

509
00:36:10.368 --> 00:36:11.903
But they can't survive
for long.

510
00:36:13.938 --> 00:36:14.906
There's more people that way.

511
00:36:19.177 --> 00:36:21.613
No badges!
Clearance badges only!

512
00:36:22.614 --> 00:36:24.582
No badges! No entry!

513
00:36:25.417 --> 00:36:27.119
Clearance badges only!

514
00:36:28.386 --> 00:36:30.288
Clearance badges only!

515
00:36:30.355 --> 00:36:31.689
We have badges!

516
00:36:31.756 --> 00:36:34.326
Hey. hey. hey. hey! Hey!

517
00:36:34.392 --> 00:36:36.728
We're governing officials
from Greenland Station!

518
00:36:36.794 --> 00:36:38.730
And we're requesting
emergency asylum!

519
00:36:38.796 --> 00:36:40.465
Give me your clearance badges!

520
00:36:40.532 --> 00:36:42.000
- Badges.
- Here. Here.

521
00:36:44.402 --> 00:36:46.138
She's clear. Come through.

522
00:36:46.204 --> 00:36:48.940
I can't find my badge!
I can't find my badge.

523
00:36:50.208 --> 00:36:51.976
Then that's it! Just her!

524
00:36:52.044 --> 00:36:53.678
Listen!
Listen. they're with us!

525
00:36:53.745 --> 00:36:55.380
One badge! One entry!

526
00:36:57.149 --> 00:36:58.383
We're Allison's family!

527
00:36:58.450 --> 00:36:59.484
My name's Adam Shaw!

528
00:36:59.551 --> 00:37:01.086
Move back!

529
00:37:01.153 --> 00:37:02.554
I'm from Thule bunker
in Greenland.

530
00:37:04.256 --> 00:37:05.857
Just run me in your system!

531
00:37:08.160 --> 00:37:10.695
I'm a governing official!
My name's Adam Shaw!

532
00:37:10.762 --> 00:37:11.929
You should find me
in your system!

533
00:37:11.996 --> 00:37:13.665
I'm a governing
official from...

534
00:37:14.966 --> 00:37:16.034
Oh. Christ!

535
00:37:17.069 --> 00:37:18.503
Let us in!

536
00:37:19.904 --> 00:37:22.574
- Back up!
- Close the gates!

537
00:37:22.640 --> 00:37:24.276
What have you done?

538
00:37:25.477 --> 00:37:26.778
Adam? Adam!

539
00:37:29.181 --> 00:37:31.216
What's happening?

540
00:37:35.353 --> 00:37:37.755
- Move! Move!
- Move! Move!

541
00:37:37.822 --> 00:37:39.023
We've gotta go.
We've gotta get out of here!

542
00:37:39.091 --> 00:37:39.991
Let's go! We've gotta go!

543
00:37:41.259 --> 00:37:44.229
All right. okay.
Casey. come on.

544
00:37:44.296 --> 00:37:46.598
- Casey!
- We've gotta go! He's gone!

545
00:37:46.664 --> 00:37:48.400
Whoa. whoa. whoa!
Yo. yo. yo. yo. yo. yo!

546
00:37:48.466 --> 00:37:50.034
Wait! No. no. no.
no. no. no. no!

547
00:37:50.102 --> 00:37:51.203
Wait. wait. wait. wait!

548
00:37:51.269 --> 00:37:53.105
- What? Move. my friend!
- We need a ride.

549
00:37:53.171 --> 00:37:54.372
I need to go.

550
00:37:54.439 --> 00:37:55.807
Oh. you've gotta take
our family. please.

551
00:37:55.873 --> 00:37:57.642
- Where?
- Uh. London. London.

552
00:37:57.709 --> 00:37:58.810
- London! Mackenzie's.
- Okay. London. London.

553
00:37:58.876 --> 00:37:59.944
You have to give me something.

554
00:38:00.011 --> 00:38:01.613
We don't have anything!

555
00:38:01.679 --> 00:38:02.714
That will do.

556
00:38:04.282 --> 00:38:05.783
- Enter.
- Go. go. go. go!

557
00:38:05.850 --> 00:38:07.219
All right. there you go.

558
00:38:26.904 --> 00:38:27.905
Thank you.

559
00:38:29.874 --> 00:38:32.244
Oh. my God. Oh. my God!

560
00:38:38.716 --> 00:38:40.051
Oh. my God.

561
00:38:42.887 --> 00:38:45.757
Hey. Hey. hey. hey. hey.
look at me.

562
00:38:45.823 --> 00:38:48.025
It's okay. it's okay.

563
00:38:48.092 --> 00:38:49.961
It's all right. Okay.
Deep breaths.

564
00:38:52.664 --> 00:38:54.065
We're gonna go to Mac's.

565
00:38:55.032 --> 00:38:56.534
Everything is gonna be okay.

566
00:38:57.502 --> 00:38:58.470
Okay?

567
00:39:00.672 --> 00:39:01.973
Is everywhere like this?

568
00:39:04.176 --> 00:39:06.378
The world is a dangerous
place now.

569
00:39:07.912 --> 00:39:09.113
People are so desperate.

570
00:39:09.181 --> 00:39:11.082
they'll kill you
for a scrap of food.

571
00:39:12.184 --> 00:39:14.619
A radiation storm
like that one.

572
00:39:14.686 --> 00:39:16.221
they come out of nowhere.

573
00:39:16.288 --> 00:39:18.190
Kill you in seconds.

574
00:39:18.256 --> 00:39:20.625
And if they don't
get you quick.

575
00:39:20.692 --> 00:39:22.727
you'll die
a slow death anyway.

576
00:39:23.895 --> 00:39:24.896
Hmm.

577
00:39:26.464 --> 00:39:27.165
Yeah...

578
00:39:28.733 --> 00:39:30.168
Great.

579
00:39:30.235 --> 00:39:32.069
The air filtration in here.
how is it?

580
00:39:32.136 --> 00:39:33.538
It works.

581
00:39:33.605 --> 00:39:36.107
but none of us are living
to a hundred. my friend.

582
00:39:39.944 --> 00:39:42.480
Babe. when was the last time
you spoke to Mackenzie?

583
00:39:42.547 --> 00:39:45.116
Um. eight or nine months ago.

584
00:40:09.574 --> 00:40:10.808
Dr. Amina?

585
00:40:12.310 --> 00:40:15.947
Do you believe it's real?
The crater?

586
00:40:16.013 --> 00:40:17.515
Yeah. I believe it's possible.

587
00:40:19.451 --> 00:40:24.956
So it is just like
the dinosaurs. the K-T event.

588
00:40:25.022 --> 00:40:27.292
Nathan. do you know what
happened after the K-T event?

589
00:40:27.359 --> 00:40:28.726
Life came back.

590
00:40:28.793 --> 00:40:29.627
Not just came back.

591
00:40:29.694 --> 00:40:31.162
It flourished.

592
00:40:32.830 --> 00:40:36.534
The impact created
the seeds for new life.

593
00:40:36.601 --> 00:40:38.169
Without the K-T event.
we wouldn't even be here.

594
00:40:41.973 --> 00:40:43.107
We are close.

595
00:40:43.174 --> 00:40:45.743
Maybe another half hour
to London.

596
00:40:45.810 --> 00:40:47.144
Let's make this quick.

597
00:40:47.211 --> 00:40:48.980
Don't wanna spend
too long outside.

598
00:40:58.490 --> 00:40:59.257
What's your name?

599
00:41:01.192 --> 00:41:02.827
Obi.

600
00:41:02.894 --> 00:41:04.061
Where are you from. Obi?

601
00:41:04.729 --> 00:41:05.697
Nigeria.

602
00:41:06.631 --> 00:41:07.965
Right.

603
00:41:08.032 --> 00:41:10.067
I moved to England
12 years ago.

604
00:41:11.836 --> 00:41:13.405
I used to hear
about life here.

605
00:41:15.206 --> 00:41:17.409
It was a childish
dream of mine.

606
00:41:17.475 --> 00:41:19.977
Well. I'm sorry this
is what you got instead.

607
00:41:20.044 --> 00:41:21.446
No. I still love it here.

608
00:41:22.880 --> 00:41:24.015
It's become my second wife.

609
00:41:25.483 --> 00:41:26.784
Though sometimes
I do wonder...

610
00:41:28.420 --> 00:41:29.621
what it would be like
to go back.

611
00:41:31.222 --> 00:41:33.224
If I'd still recognize
anything at all.

612
00:41:35.493 --> 00:41:37.462
Mmm.

613
00:41:37.529 --> 00:41:39.997
What do you hear about people
heading further south.

614
00:41:40.064 --> 00:41:41.466
over into France?

615
00:41:44.836 --> 00:41:47.372
France is more dangerous
than here.

616
00:41:47.439 --> 00:41:49.106
Is that because
of what's over there?

617
00:41:49.173 --> 00:41:52.377
You mean the stuff
your scientist friend there was talking about?

618
00:41:52.444 --> 00:41:54.512
- Yeah.
- Sounds nice.

619
00:41:54.579 --> 00:41:56.881
Also sounds like <i>ashi gi.</i>

620
00:41:59.684 --> 00:42:00.418
Bullshit.

621
00:42:06.558 --> 00:42:07.659
You good?

622
00:42:07.725 --> 00:42:09.160
Yeah.

623
00:42:21.105 --> 00:42:21.906
Whoa. what is that?

624
00:42:22.640 --> 00:42:23.808
Another storm?

625
00:42:23.875 --> 00:42:25.276
No. that's not a storm.

626
00:42:33.785 --> 00:42:34.886
Allison!

627
00:42:34.952 --> 00:42:35.987
Grab onto something!

628
00:42:38.089 --> 00:42:39.290
Come. come!

629
00:42:42.159 --> 00:42:43.294
There.

630
00:43:12.690 --> 00:43:14.058
Obi! No!

631
00:43:14.125 --> 00:43:15.192
It's all I have!

632
00:43:35.780 --> 00:43:37.749
- You okay?
- Yeah.

633
00:44:32.403 --> 00:44:33.771
I hope she's still here.

634
00:44:40.244 --> 00:44:42.213
- Mac!
- Oh. sh...

635
00:44:43.881 --> 00:44:46.618
Bloody hell! Bloody...

636
00:44:46.684 --> 00:44:48.185
- Get inside! Come!
- Mac!

637
00:44:48.252 --> 00:44:50.221
- Get inside!
- Is that loaded?

638
00:44:50.287 --> 00:44:52.223
- Oh!
- Hi.

639
00:44:52.289 --> 00:44:53.290
Get inside!

640
00:44:55.693 --> 00:44:59.030
How are you on my doorstep
right now?

641
00:44:59.096 --> 00:45:01.165
I haven't heard from you
for so long!

642
00:45:01.232 --> 00:45:03.034
I was beginning
to fear the worst.

643
00:45:03.100 --> 00:45:07.672
Oh. and John! I never thought
I'd see that ugly mug again!

644
00:45:07.739 --> 00:45:08.873
- Oh...
- You're looking good. Mac.

645
00:45:08.940 --> 00:45:10.542
Oh. liar.

646
00:45:10.608 --> 00:45:13.077
Oh. this must be the man. yes!

647
00:45:13.144 --> 00:45:15.412
You're all your mum
ever talks about!

648
00:45:15.479 --> 00:45:16.681
- Really?
- Yeah.

649
00:45:16.748 --> 00:45:18.816
Nearly all. I think.

650
00:45:18.883 --> 00:45:21.719
Honestly. I can't believe
my eyes.

651
00:45:21.786 --> 00:45:24.421
Oh. wow. You're celebrating
Christmas early.

652
00:45:24.488 --> 00:45:26.591
Oh. every day
is Christmas here.

653
00:45:26.658 --> 00:45:28.760
Here. just put your bags
down anywhere

654
00:45:28.826 --> 00:45:30.194
and just make yourselves
at home.

655
00:45:30.261 --> 00:45:32.396
Honestly. I can't believe...

656
00:45:32.463 --> 00:45:36.701
Um. also the air is really
a lot better than the outside.

657
00:45:36.768 --> 00:45:39.336
I managed to seal off
this wing of the hospital

658
00:45:39.403 --> 00:45:44.108
and the generator keeps
the filtration system going.

659
00:45:44.175 --> 00:45:46.210
It's not as good as the air
you're used to in the bunkers.

660
00:45:46.277 --> 00:45:48.212
but it'll give us
a few more years.

661
00:45:48.279 --> 00:45:49.513
- Thank you.
- Please. no.

662
00:45:49.581 --> 00:45:50.915
You're family. honestly.

663
00:45:50.982 --> 00:45:53.785
I mean. I dream about our time
in the States.

664
00:45:53.851 --> 00:45:55.252
Those American boys.

665
00:45:55.319 --> 00:45:57.555
They're suckers for an accent.

666
00:45:57.622 --> 00:45:59.390
Ah. So are the girls.

667
00:46:01.759 --> 00:46:03.728
- Hey.
- What are you treating here?

668
00:46:03.795 --> 00:46:04.896
Oh. Alzheimer's.

669
00:46:04.962 --> 00:46:07.264
And. well. broken hearts.

670
00:46:07.331 --> 00:46:08.365
Most of them have no idea

671
00:46:08.432 --> 00:46:09.433
what happened
to their families

672
00:46:09.500 --> 00:46:11.569
or anything about the comet.

673
00:46:11.636 --> 00:46:12.503
Which is probably
just as well.

674
00:46:13.337 --> 00:46:14.639
So I stayed on.

675
00:46:14.706 --> 00:46:17.208
Even when the government
stopped delivering food

676
00:46:17.274 --> 00:46:19.443
and the lights turned off.

677
00:46:19.510 --> 00:46:21.312
I won't let them
be abandoned again.

678
00:46:23.981 --> 00:46:25.316
Actually. speaking of which.

679
00:46:25.382 --> 00:46:26.884
it's time I prepped
their supper.

680
00:46:26.951 --> 00:46:28.052
Oh well. I'll help.

681
00:46:28.119 --> 00:46:29.654
Oh. that's so kind. Thank you.

682
00:46:29.721 --> 00:46:31.723
Hey John. um. you and Nathan
grab some more coals.

683
00:46:31.789 --> 00:46:34.792
I feel like celebrating!

684
00:46:40.464 --> 00:46:42.166
Run back in.
Oh. my God. just...

685
00:46:42.233 --> 00:46:43.635
Whoa. it's amazing!

686
00:46:43.701 --> 00:46:45.102
Okay. How's this?

687
00:46:46.738 --> 00:46:48.339
See? That's still better.

688
00:46:48.405 --> 00:46:51.776
We finally spoke.
this is finally...

689
00:46:53.177 --> 00:46:55.312
- Cheers everybody.
- Cheers!

690
00:46:57.815 --> 00:47:00.351
Guys. this almost
feels normal. Almost.

691
00:47:00.417 --> 00:47:02.019
Yeah. Almost.

692
00:47:07.191 --> 00:47:09.126
Oh. he's still sleeping?

693
00:47:09.193 --> 00:47:12.529
Ah. that's good.
Poor kid is exhausted.

694
00:47:12.596 --> 00:47:14.331
Does he remember
the impact at all?

695
00:47:14.398 --> 00:47:16.133
Yeah. he does.

696
00:47:16.200 --> 00:47:17.935
I was hoping he would forget
with time. but he hasn't.

697
00:47:18.002 --> 00:47:20.705
He's just...
I guess he's still processing.

698
00:47:20.772 --> 00:47:22.774
God. you can't put Clarke
in a box.

699
00:47:22.840 --> 00:47:24.175
Not when you're reminded
of it every time

700
00:47:24.241 --> 00:47:25.677
you look out the window.

701
00:47:25.743 --> 00:47:29.346
What do you know. Mac.
about the crater?

702
00:47:29.413 --> 00:47:31.382
You know. the...
where Clarke hit?

703
00:47:32.917 --> 00:47:34.285
Are you thinking of buying
a holiday home?

704
00:47:36.387 --> 00:47:39.023
No. I've just heard rumors.
just a load of rumors.

705
00:47:39.090 --> 00:47:41.458
No. because Casey thinks
there's a possibility

706
00:47:41.525 --> 00:47:42.559
life returned there. right?

707
00:47:42.626 --> 00:47:44.796
Yeah. I do. Yeah.

708
00:47:44.862 --> 00:47:47.598
Let's say you have extremely
high temperatures. right?

709
00:47:48.966 --> 00:47:52.203
And you added in raw materials
and. uh.

710
00:47:52.269 --> 00:47:54.538
the ocean water
from the tsunami.

711
00:47:54.605 --> 00:47:56.407
Throw in some
terrigenous nutrients

712
00:47:56.473 --> 00:47:58.209
from the rocks smashed
during impact.

713
00:47:58.275 --> 00:48:02.046
then it's possible
you could. uh...

714
00:48:02.113 --> 00:48:03.848
You could create the building
blocks for new life.

715
00:48:05.249 --> 00:48:06.250
Mmm.

716
00:48:07.318 --> 00:48:08.285
Breathable air.

717
00:48:09.921 --> 00:48:12.256
Drinkable water.
It's... it's possible.

718
00:48:13.825 --> 00:48:15.993
That's a nice thought.

719
00:48:16.060 --> 00:48:21.498
But. um. you know.
what I've made here is.

720
00:48:21.565 --> 00:48:24.568
it's good enough
to survive these days.

721
00:48:24.635 --> 00:48:26.738
And it's safe. you know?

722
00:48:26.804 --> 00:48:28.239
I've made it safe.

723
00:48:30.074 --> 00:48:31.375
Oh...

724
00:48:31.442 --> 00:48:34.545
Okay. safer than outside.

725
00:48:34.611 --> 00:48:36.013
Hey!

726
00:48:36.080 --> 00:48:37.782
London isn't
London anymore.

727
00:49:01.538 --> 00:49:04.108
- John. are you okay?
- Yeah. yeah.

728
00:49:04.175 --> 00:49:05.877
- Oh. my God. you're bleeding.
- Yeah.

729
00:49:06.844 --> 00:49:08.345
Yeah. Must be the air.

730
00:49:09.113 --> 00:49:09.914
Nosebleed.

731
00:49:10.948 --> 00:49:11.883
John...

732
00:49:14.185 --> 00:49:15.052
What's going on?

733
00:49:16.487 --> 00:49:17.855
Just... I've got a nosebleed.

734
00:49:22.059 --> 00:49:22.760
Bullshit.

735
00:49:25.863 --> 00:49:28.465
The doctor said. um...

736
00:49:28.532 --> 00:49:31.335
when symptoms start...
bleeding...

737
00:49:33.504 --> 00:49:34.705
six to eight weeks.

738
00:49:41.478 --> 00:49:43.514
Six weeks? What?

739
00:49:43.580 --> 00:49:44.949
I mean. it may be more. I...

740
00:49:45.016 --> 00:49:47.484
What are you talking about?
That can't be right.

741
00:49:47.551 --> 00:49:49.987
We're here now. with Mac.
She has medicine.

742
00:49:50.054 --> 00:49:51.688
I'm sure we can get
you the right medication.

743
00:49:51.755 --> 00:49:53.290
- Ali. no. Ali...
- And everything will be okay.

744
00:49:53.357 --> 00:49:54.358
Ali...

745
00:49:57.394 --> 00:49:58.595
It's not fixable.

746
00:49:59.696 --> 00:50:00.798
What do you mean?

747
00:50:04.401 --> 00:50:05.736
It's...

748
00:50:07.738 --> 00:50:09.640
Too many trips outside. I guess.

749
00:50:10.942 --> 00:50:13.177
Why didn't you tell me?

750
00:50:13.244 --> 00:50:14.511
- I wanted to...
- John!

751
00:50:14.578 --> 00:50:15.880
I wanted to...

752
00:50:15.947 --> 00:50:17.481
Why?

753
00:50:17.548 --> 00:50:18.782
Because I couldn't see this...

754
00:50:18.850 --> 00:50:20.852
I couldn't see this from you.
I couldn't...

755
00:50:20.918 --> 00:50:23.654
Okay. all right.
Okay. okay. okay.

756
00:50:26.357 --> 00:50:27.058
Look at me.

757
00:50:27.791 --> 00:50:28.759
Okay.

758
00:50:30.962 --> 00:50:34.899
Okay. We're gonna stay here.
with Mac.

759
00:50:34.966 --> 00:50:36.901
And we're gonna take
this time that we have left

760
00:50:36.968 --> 00:50:40.371
and we're gonna be together
as a family.

761
00:50:40.437 --> 00:50:41.873
We can't stay here. Ali.

762
00:50:41.939 --> 00:50:43.975
I don't wanna stay here.

763
00:50:44.041 --> 00:50:45.342
I don't wanna die here.

764
00:50:46.911 --> 00:50:48.812
I don't want you and Nathan
to live here.

765
00:50:48.880 --> 00:50:51.482
We didn't come all this way
for this!

766
00:50:52.816 --> 00:50:54.585
I mean. what if Casey's right?

767
00:50:55.486 --> 00:50:57.989
About the crater.

768
00:50:58.055 --> 00:51:03.594
There's something there.
like a fresh. a new beginning.

769
00:51:03.660 --> 00:51:05.897
For you. For our son.

770
00:51:05.963 --> 00:51:09.533
Half of his life
has been surviving.

771
00:51:09.600 --> 00:51:11.768
We have to get Nathan
to the crater.

772
00:51:11.835 --> 00:51:13.670
I know.

773
00:51:13.737 --> 00:51:14.805
There's no life for him here.

774
00:51:17.608 --> 00:51:19.176
- Okay.
- Okay.

775
00:51:28.452 --> 00:51:30.955
<i>You're sure you're okay
with us taking this?</i>

776
00:51:31.022 --> 00:51:33.090
Oh. well. I took it
from someone else.

777
00:51:33.157 --> 00:51:35.226
And it should have enough fuel
to get you to the Channel.

778
00:51:35.292 --> 00:51:36.727
- Yeah.
- Take this.

779
00:51:36.793 --> 00:51:39.063
And don't stop for anyone.

780
00:51:39.130 --> 00:51:42.033
You're gonna wanna head
down through Dover.

781
00:51:42.099 --> 00:51:43.767
It's the only place you'll
be able to cross the Channel.

782
00:51:43.834 --> 00:51:44.835
Thank you.

783
00:51:45.836 --> 00:51:46.837
Oh...

784
00:51:47.204 --> 00:51:48.472
Okay.

785
00:51:53.044 --> 00:51:54.378
- Take care of my girl!
- I will.

786
00:51:55.612 --> 00:51:56.747
Oh. Nate...

787
00:51:58.115 --> 00:51:59.650
- Nice to meet you.
- Bye. Nate.

788
00:52:22.573 --> 00:52:25.977
Okay.
So according to this map.

789
00:52:26.043 --> 00:52:27.878
we should get there
in about two hours.

790
00:52:34.051 --> 00:52:35.052
You're very quiet there. bud.

791
00:52:36.587 --> 00:52:38.822
You remember we used to play
those car games?

792
00:52:38.889 --> 00:52:40.124
Back when you were little?

793
00:52:40.191 --> 00:52:41.458
Yeah. I remember.

794
00:52:41.525 --> 00:52:43.860
Like "I Spy"...

795
00:52:43.927 --> 00:52:45.662
- "Would You Rather"...
- That was my favorite.

796
00:52:45.729 --> 00:52:47.164
You know. my sister and I.

797
00:52:47.231 --> 00:52:48.632
we used to play 21 Questions
on road trips.

798
00:52:48.699 --> 00:52:49.866
Do you remember that one?

799
00:52:49.933 --> 00:52:51.135
Go on.
what do you say. Nathan?

800
00:52:51.202 --> 00:52:52.503
- You wanna play?
- No thanks.

801
00:52:52.569 --> 00:52:54.538
You know what? Let's play
anyway. without him.

802
00:52:54.605 --> 00:52:56.440
- Yeah!
- I wanna play I Spy though.

803
00:52:56.507 --> 00:52:57.708
I'll go first.

804
00:52:57.774 --> 00:52:59.110
No. I'll go first.

805
00:52:59.176 --> 00:53:00.344
- I'm gonna go first.
- Okay...

806
00:53:04.681 --> 00:53:06.550
- Oh. my...
- Casey...

807
00:53:08.352 --> 00:53:10.054
Get down. Nathan!

808
00:53:10.121 --> 00:53:11.522
Nathan. get down! Stay down!

809
00:53:11.588 --> 00:53:13.890
Don't shoot the engine!
We need that car!

810
00:53:15.359 --> 00:53:17.661
- Move forward! Move!
- Who are they?

811
00:53:17.728 --> 00:53:19.763
Marauders! Nathan. stay down!

812
00:53:21.232 --> 00:53:23.567
Ah... Go. go.

813
00:53:56.400 --> 00:53:58.702
It's okay. it's okay.

814
00:53:58.769 --> 00:54:01.004
It's okay. it's okay.

815
00:54:01.072 --> 00:54:03.707
It's okay. it's okay.
It's okay.

816
00:54:03.774 --> 00:54:05.976
Nathan? Nathan? Nathan?

817
00:54:07.144 --> 00:54:10.181
Nathan. are you okay?
You okay?

818
00:54:11.615 --> 00:54:12.983
Okay. There you go.

819
00:54:49.019 --> 00:54:50.887
May the Lord rise to meet you.

820
00:54:52.289 --> 00:54:55.559
May the wind be always
at your back.

821
00:54:55.626 --> 00:54:59.263
May the sun shine warm
upon your face.

822
00:54:59.330 --> 00:55:01.598
And may the rains fall softly
upon your fields.

823
00:55:09.140 --> 00:55:11.041
Why do people say prayers
at funerals?

824
00:55:13.977 --> 00:55:16.513
It sounds like
you're wishing them well.

825
00:55:17.848 --> 00:55:19.250
And they're dead.

826
00:55:19.316 --> 00:55:21.352
Well. you are...
wishing them well.

827
00:55:22.853 --> 00:55:23.920
It's an old tradition.

828
00:55:27.258 --> 00:55:30.194
Same reason they put coins
over the eyes.

829
00:55:30.261 --> 00:55:32.996
- Coins?
- Bribe the ferryman.

830
00:55:33.063 --> 00:55:35.299
Crossing the river
to the world of the dead.

831
00:55:39.002 --> 00:55:40.437
Even if they don't believe
in heaven?

832
00:55:48.712 --> 00:55:50.147
Even if they don't believe
in heaven.

833
00:56:21.044 --> 00:56:22.579
Is that the English Channel?

834
00:56:23.714 --> 00:56:24.915
It was.

835
00:56:26.583 --> 00:56:29.052
Jesus.

836
00:56:29.119 --> 00:56:31.054
My dad used to take us
over here to France

837
00:56:31.121 --> 00:56:33.257
on a ferry when I was a kid.

838
00:56:33.324 --> 00:56:36.327
- And that was all water?
- Oh. yeah.

839
00:56:36.393 --> 00:56:39.363
Twenty miles of sea
from here to France.

840
00:56:39.430 --> 00:56:41.332
There's so many battles.

841
00:56:41.398 --> 00:56:43.133
there's so many wars
fought over this.

842
00:56:43.900 --> 00:56:45.135
It's all gone.

843
00:56:47.404 --> 00:56:50.674
Well. at least we don't have
to take a boat.

844
00:56:50.741 --> 00:56:52.543
Exactly.
Let's get across this quick

845
00:56:52.609 --> 00:56:54.044
and find a place
for the night.

846
00:57:15.832 --> 00:57:17.534
Is that a Spanish galleon?

847
00:57:44.628 --> 00:57:46.029
What are they all stopped for?

848
00:57:47.898 --> 00:57:48.765
I don't know.

849
00:58:01.512 --> 00:58:02.879
I guess we're leaving the car.

850
00:58:13.256 --> 00:58:15.091
We're gonna cross that?

851
00:58:15.158 --> 00:58:16.593
Yeah. We're gonna have to.

852
00:58:42.185 --> 00:58:43.820
Watch your step now.

853
00:58:43.887 --> 00:58:45.489
- I've got you.
- Come on!

854
00:58:52.363 --> 00:58:54.898
Watch your step. Watch.
Don't look down.

855
00:59:00.737 --> 00:59:02.473
- Ah!
- Careful!

856
00:59:04.775 --> 00:59:08.144
Okay. Tighten up. everybody.
Make sure we're secure.

857
00:59:08.211 --> 00:59:11.682
No. I can't. I can't do this.

858
00:59:11.748 --> 00:59:14.017
I can't... I can't do this!
There's gotta be another way!

859
00:59:14.084 --> 00:59:16.019
Nathan! Just put one foot
in front of the other.

860
00:59:16.086 --> 00:59:17.788
Just follow me.
I'll go first. okay?

861
00:59:18.755 --> 00:59:20.424
You've got this.

862
00:59:20.491 --> 00:59:22.058
All right. come on.

863
00:59:22.125 --> 00:59:23.860
- All right.
- You good?

864
00:59:23.927 --> 00:59:26.229
- Okay. You've got this.
- Be careful.

865
00:59:26.296 --> 00:59:27.364
Okay.

866
00:59:50.353 --> 00:59:52.322
Just keep going! Go!

867
00:59:54.791 --> 00:59:56.527
You good?

868
00:59:56.593 --> 00:59:57.894
Go. go. go!

869
01:00:08.772 --> 01:00:09.640
Ahhh!

870
01:00:10.874 --> 01:00:12.008
Hang on!

871
01:00:19.382 --> 01:00:21.351
- Everything okay?
- Yeah. Dad.

872
01:00:27.991 --> 01:00:29.526
Come on. Atta boy.

873
01:00:31.127 --> 01:00:32.062
Yeah.

874
01:00:32.829 --> 01:00:34.297
Okay.

875
01:00:34.364 --> 01:00:35.398
That's good.

876
01:00:37.501 --> 01:00:39.736
Come on. you've got it!
You've got it!

877
01:00:39.803 --> 01:00:42.739
Oh! Thank you.

878
01:00:42.806 --> 01:00:44.808
Right. almost there.
Just a little bit more.

879
01:00:44.875 --> 01:00:45.942
- You got it?
- Yeah.

880
01:00:46.009 --> 01:00:47.377
- You good?
- Yeah.

881
01:00:48.244 --> 01:00:49.580
That's it.

882
01:00:49.646 --> 01:00:51.815
Earthquake!

883
01:00:51.882 --> 01:00:53.950
Get down!

884
01:00:54.017 --> 01:00:56.386
- You've gotta be kidding me.
- We've gotta get off of here!

885
01:00:56.853 --> 01:00:58.955
Let's go.

886
01:00:59.022 --> 01:01:00.991
You go first. Allison.
I'll go behind Nathan.

887
01:01:01.057 --> 01:01:02.459
Just stay focused.

888
01:01:05.562 --> 01:01:07.363
That's it. You're okay!

889
01:01:12.235 --> 01:01:13.970
That's it. There you go.

890
01:01:17.040 --> 01:01:18.408
That's it. Nathan!

891
01:01:28.418 --> 01:01:30.420
- The line is breaking!
- Hang on!

892
01:01:36.126 --> 01:01:37.994
- Let's go!
- Get me off!

893
01:01:38.061 --> 01:01:39.663
Keep moving!

894
01:01:39.730 --> 01:01:42.365
Get me off of this!
Get me off!

895
01:01:45.301 --> 01:01:47.370
Keep moving!

896
01:01:47.437 --> 01:01:48.872
- It won't hold!
- No. no. no. no. no!

897
01:01:48.939 --> 01:01:50.073
It won't hold!

898
01:01:50.140 --> 01:01:52.142
- Stay there! No!
- No! No!

899
01:01:52.208 --> 01:01:53.443
Nathan!

900
01:01:55.111 --> 01:01:56.880
- Nathan!
- Dad. Dad!

901
01:01:56.947 --> 01:01:58.649
Come on! Hold on!

902
01:02:00.116 --> 01:02:02.085
You've got it! It's okay.

903
01:02:02.152 --> 01:02:03.654
Please don't let me fall!

904
01:02:03.720 --> 01:02:06.222
- Hold on!
- Nathan! Nathan!

905
01:02:06.289 --> 01:02:07.858
Don't let me fall!

906
01:02:09.960 --> 01:02:11.394
Come on! That's it!

907
01:02:11.461 --> 01:02:13.463
It won't hold!

908
01:02:14.898 --> 01:02:16.533
- Nathan! Keep moving!
- Come on!

909
01:02:16.600 --> 01:02:19.369
Come on. you've gotta go.
That's it.

910
01:02:19.435 --> 01:02:21.304
Come on. kiddo! Almost there.

911
01:02:22.272 --> 01:02:23.674
Come on. Nathan!

912
01:02:23.740 --> 01:02:25.141
Hurry!

913
01:02:26.009 --> 01:02:27.110
Take my hand!

914
01:02:28.178 --> 01:02:29.012
Don't look down!

915
01:02:31.948 --> 01:02:34.217
Come on! Okay. let's go!
Let's go. Let's go. Nathan.

916
01:02:34.284 --> 01:02:36.152
Come on! That's it.

917
01:02:37.287 --> 01:02:38.288
Come on!

918
01:02:44.094 --> 01:02:45.128
Oh. my God!

919
01:03:24.735 --> 01:03:25.568
What the hell?

920
01:03:40.416 --> 01:03:42.252
- Is that it?
- No. That's not it.

921
01:03:42.318 --> 01:03:43.386
It's much further south.

922
01:03:44.220 --> 01:03:46.356
It's totally dead.

923
01:03:46.422 --> 01:03:48.191
What if the Clarke
crater's like this?

924
01:03:48.258 --> 01:03:50.861
This could've been a fragment
that hit a week ago.

925
01:03:50.927 --> 01:03:51.862
Or five years ago.

926
01:03:52.996 --> 01:03:53.964
Hey...

927
01:03:56.032 --> 01:03:57.734
This is what we're doing.
We're gonna keep going.

928
01:04:00.436 --> 01:04:01.805
- Yeah.
- Okay.

929
01:04:09.746 --> 01:04:11.648
Uh... English?

930
01:04:13.016 --> 01:04:14.550
Who are you?

931
01:04:14.617 --> 01:04:16.386
My name is. uh. John Garrity.

932
01:04:18.088 --> 01:04:19.055
This is my wife. Allison.

933
01:04:19.122 --> 01:04:20.290
My son. Nathan.

934
01:04:21.357 --> 01:04:22.826
What are you doing here?

935
01:04:22.893 --> 01:04:24.895
We're trying to get
to the Clarke Crater.

936
01:04:38.308 --> 01:04:39.442
I am Denis Laurent.

937
01:04:40.143 --> 01:04:41.511
Hi.

938
01:04:42.612 --> 01:04:43.613
You look hungry.

939
01:04:45.548 --> 01:04:46.850
We don't have
anything to trade.

940
01:04:48.251 --> 01:04:49.419
Ah. but you do.

941
01:04:50.453 --> 01:04:51.621
It's called company.

942
01:05:00.096 --> 01:05:01.998
So. do you always
shoot at people?

943
01:05:02.065 --> 01:05:04.000
It's a dangerous area.

944
01:05:04.067 --> 01:05:05.568
You're lucky I found you.

945
01:05:05.635 --> 01:05:07.337
Most people aren't so nice.

946
01:05:30.426 --> 01:05:31.494
This is us.

947
01:05:32.595 --> 01:05:33.663
What was this place?

948
01:05:34.931 --> 01:05:38.534
This is
our mail sorting center.

949
01:05:38.601 --> 01:05:40.470
Nobody tries to take
this from you?

950
01:05:41.704 --> 01:05:42.705
They've tried.

951
01:05:45.541 --> 01:05:47.944
This is your
power supply. You built this?

952
01:05:48.011 --> 01:05:50.446
Yes. We draw power
from the solar panels

953
01:05:50.513 --> 01:05:53.416
into the car's power bank.
and we have electricity.

954
01:05:53.483 --> 01:05:55.251
It powers our air purifiers.

955
01:05:55.318 --> 01:05:57.720
It's not perfect.
but it's the best we can do.

956
01:06:07.730 --> 01:06:09.866
John. Allison. Nathan...

957
01:06:12.535 --> 01:06:13.703
And my daughter. Camille.

958
01:06:15.305 --> 01:06:16.272
Nice to meet you.

959
01:06:17.540 --> 01:06:18.508
She does not speak.

960
01:06:18.574 --> 01:06:19.843
Her nervous system.

961
01:06:19.910 --> 01:06:21.711
The radiation
has taken its toll.

962
01:06:24.714 --> 01:06:26.616
Very good.

963
01:06:26.682 --> 01:06:28.251
- Yeah. <i>c'est bon.</i>
- It's good. yeah.

964
01:06:28.318 --> 01:06:29.953
Closest thing you get to
a French restaurant today.

965
01:06:30.020 --> 01:06:31.687
Thank you so much.

966
01:06:31.754 --> 01:06:32.856
- It's great.
- Very good.

967
01:06:32.923 --> 01:06:34.858
It's very nice
to have a home-cooked meal.

968
01:06:34.925 --> 01:06:38.328
So. you are trying
to reach the crater?

969
01:06:38.394 --> 01:06:40.063
- Yeah.
- Yeah. we are.

970
01:06:40.130 --> 01:06:42.632
They say the crater
is <i>La Terre Promise...</i>

971
01:06:42.698 --> 01:06:45.869
how you say...
The Promised Land.

972
01:06:45.936 --> 01:06:47.537
Humanity's last chance.

973
01:06:49.339 --> 01:06:50.506
It could be so.

974
01:06:50.573 --> 01:06:52.508
We've also heard that...

975
01:06:52.575 --> 01:06:54.410
maybe people have gone there.

976
01:06:55.545 --> 01:06:57.447
That region is too dangerous.

977
01:06:57.513 --> 01:06:58.949
The Western Alliance.

978
01:06:59.015 --> 01:07:01.484
including remnants
of the French Army.

979
01:07:01.551 --> 01:07:03.053
are defending it
from an invasion

980
01:07:03.119 --> 01:07:05.021
by the Eastern Coalition.

981
01:07:05.088 --> 01:07:07.891
who want to take the crater
for its resources.

982
01:07:07.958 --> 01:07:09.759
There is heavy fighting
on the entire front.

983
01:07:11.561 --> 01:07:12.562
From Lyon to Berne.

984
01:07:13.596 --> 01:07:15.231
Only two cities left standing.

985
01:07:16.566 --> 01:07:18.268
It is impossible
to get through.

986
01:07:22.372 --> 01:07:24.841
Where'd you get
all these things?

987
01:07:24.908 --> 01:07:26.709
My dad sometimes
will go outside

988
01:07:26.776 --> 01:07:29.345
and try to find stuff that
was not completely destroyed.

989
01:07:30.613 --> 01:07:31.781
So we could make a home.

990
01:07:34.550 --> 01:07:36.086
Can I show you something?

991
01:07:36.152 --> 01:07:37.420
Sure.

992
01:07:37.487 --> 01:07:39.990
I made this in the bunker.
in Greenland.

993
01:07:40.056 --> 01:07:44.227
It's. um. it's the sky
we can never see.

994
01:07:44.294 --> 01:07:47.497
It's what we would have seen
if we... we could've seen.

995
01:07:47.563 --> 01:07:48.798
You hold that end.

996
01:07:50.066 --> 01:07:52.802
- Which one? Oh...
- Oh. sorry. Okay.

997
01:07:56.272 --> 01:07:58.841
- You come down as well. yeah.
- Oh. okay.

998
01:08:03.479 --> 01:08:05.548
So. these are the star signs.

999
01:08:05.615 --> 01:08:06.816
Do you know what
star sign you are?

1000
01:08:07.918 --> 01:08:09.552
I think I'm Aquarius.

1001
01:08:09.619 --> 01:08:11.621
Oh. that's air.

1002
01:08:11.687 --> 01:08:13.456
- I'm a Pisces.
- Mmm...

1003
01:08:13.523 --> 01:08:14.357
So I'm a fish.

1004
01:08:16.526 --> 01:08:18.428
I read somewhere that...

1005
01:08:18.494 --> 01:08:20.496
that Pisces and Aquariuses
get along well.

1006
01:08:47.157 --> 01:08:49.459
Oh... hey.

1007
01:08:49.525 --> 01:08:50.826
Hi.

1008
01:08:50.893 --> 01:08:52.328
How long have you been up for?

1009
01:08:53.964 --> 01:08:56.032
- Most of the night.
- Oh...

1010
01:08:57.233 --> 01:08:58.068
Oh.

1011
01:09:01.137 --> 01:09:04.140
Hey. the night before
our wedding...

1012
01:09:04.207 --> 01:09:06.409
My dad took you aside
into this little side room

1013
01:09:06.476 --> 01:09:07.177
or whatever it was.

1014
01:09:09.345 --> 01:09:10.813
He told me he loved me.

1015
01:09:10.880 --> 01:09:12.882
Like a son.

1016
01:09:15.085 --> 01:09:16.352
What did he really say to you?

1017
01:09:21.857 --> 01:09:23.559
Oh. he made me
promise something.

1018
01:09:28.531 --> 01:09:29.899
That I would
take care of you...

1019
01:09:31.601 --> 01:09:33.069
until my last breath.

1020
01:09:39.775 --> 01:09:41.144
Oh. hey...

1021
01:10:18.048 --> 01:10:21.584
This one...
is more up to date than yours.

1022
01:10:21.651 --> 01:10:24.387
The Western Alliance
defends the crater

1023
01:10:24.454 --> 01:10:26.922
so people can live there
as a free society.

1024
01:10:26.989 --> 01:10:28.491
As I said last night.

1025
01:10:28.558 --> 01:10:31.061
this entire region
is a heavy war zone.

1026
01:10:31.127 --> 01:10:33.696
but there is a way around.

1027
01:10:33.763 --> 01:10:36.166
I recommend you take this way.

1028
01:10:36.232 --> 01:10:36.966
Clermont-Ferrand.

1029
01:10:38.601 --> 01:10:39.769
Then down to Valence.

1030
01:10:40.736 --> 01:10:42.405
Less fighting.

1031
01:10:42.472 --> 01:10:45.375
The crater is protected
by several mountain ranges.

1032
01:10:45.441 --> 01:10:47.843
Through the first.
there is only one way.

1033
01:10:48.478 --> 01:10:49.479
The pass.

1034
01:10:51.481 --> 01:10:54.617
It will be very difficult
to move through this area.

1035
01:10:54.684 --> 01:10:57.120
The pass is protected by
my friend's battalion.

1036
01:10:57.187 --> 01:10:58.754
of the Western Alliance.

1037
01:10:58.821 --> 01:11:00.423
So when you get there.

1038
01:11:00.490 --> 01:11:02.392
you will ask
for Commander Jeunet.

1039
01:11:02.458 --> 01:11:03.759
Jeunet.

1040
01:11:03.826 --> 01:11:05.895
And you will give him this.

1041
01:11:07.830 --> 01:11:09.199
He'll know I sent you.

1042
01:11:10.433 --> 01:11:11.634
He can get you through.

1043
01:11:15.805 --> 01:11:17.006
Thank you.

1044
